reviews.review_text: rating shows bias This venue was (it no longer exists) an echo chamber and sometimes a painful experience to hear music. Don't know how the tapers (Minches/Severson) got such a prime recording but it captures the GD sound and the shows energy. I like it better than the other copy for some reason. Weir vocals stand out. Like many aud recordings the bass is lacking. 2nd set has a driven sound. Somewhere I read Garcia stating that the perfect Stella Blue should have moments of silence. This one is a good example. I was mesmerized on this night.

Nice AUD Recording As a admitted SBD/matrix snob, I have been going through some of these early 80's AUDs and I have to admit, there are some very listenable, deep sounding captures that I am downloading happily.
